'''Bochasan''' is a small town in [[Gujarat]], western [[India]]. It is known primarily as the origin of [[Bochasanwasi Shri Akshar Purushottam Swaminarayan Sanstha]] (BAPS), so named because its first formal center was established in Bochasan in 1907 by its guru Shastriji Maharaj.
