'''Brendan Callaghan''' [[Society of Jesus|SJ]] (born 29 July 1948) is a [[psychology of religion|psychologist of religion]] who was Master of [[Campion Hall, Oxford]] 2008–13. He was Principal of [[Heythrop College, London]] 1985–97.<ref name="whoswho">[http://www.ukwhoswho.com/view/article/oupww/whoswho/U9899 CALLAGHAN, Rev. Brendan Alphonsus], ''Who's Who 2015'', A & C Black, 2015; online edn, Oxford University Press, 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.heythrop.ac.uk/about-us/college-staff/academic-staff/brendan-callaghan-sj.html Heythrop College biography.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100718191544/http://www.heythrop.ac.uk/about-us/college-staff/academic-staff/brendan-callaghan-sj.html |date=18 July 2010 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.ox.ac.uk/about_the_university/introducing_oxford/annual_review/annual_review_20078/new_appointments/new_heads_of_house.html New Heads of Houses, Oxford University Annual Review 2007/08.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609220545/http://www.ox.ac.uk/about_the_university/introducing_oxford/annual_review/annual_review_20078/new_appointments/new_heads_of_house.html |date=9 June 2011 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/2997/Brendan-Alphonsus-CALLAGHAN The Rev Brendan Callaghan, SJ]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, ''Debrett's People of Today''</ref>

